</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/trump-zelenskyy-white-house-meeting-high-stakes.png" alt="A high-stakes White House meeting between President Donald Trump and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>A high-stakes White House meeting between President Donald Trump and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy. Credits: ABC News</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           High-level ceasefire talks in London between Ukraine, the US, and European allies were <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-04-2025-h1-1-downgraded" target="_blank">downgraded</a> after US Secretary of State Marco Rubio withdrew, reportedly due to Ukraine’s refusal to cede territory to Russia.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          According to the proposed peace plan:</p>
          <ul style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;list-style:none;padding:0px 8px;">
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span> Washington will recognize the occupation of Ukrainian territories in Luhansk, Donetsk, Kherson, and Zaporizhzhia regions</li>
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span>Ukraine will be prevented from joining NATO, but will be permitted to join the EU</li>
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span>Ukraine will lift sanctions imposed on Russia since 2014</li>
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span>The US will develop deeper energy and economic cooperation with Russia</li>
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span>Ukraine will have a "robust security guarantee" backed by European countries, the right to navigate the Dnieper River, and assistance with rebuilding</li>
            <li><span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin-right:8px">→</span>Ukraine will recognize Russia's annexation of Crimea</li>
          </ul>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;"> 
          President Zelenskyy reiterated that Ukraine will not recognize Russia’s annexation of Crimea or hold peace talks without a complete ceasefire.</p>
        
        </mj-text>
