          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇷🇺 Russia-Iran strategic treaty signed into law</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">President Putin <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-04-2025-br2-6-signed-a-law" target="_blank">signed a law</a> ratifying a 20-year strategic partnership agreement with Iran, strengthening ties in defense, intelligence, and energy. The treaty was initially signed in January with Iranian President Pezeshkian. Key elements of the agreement include cooperation on military drills, officer training, arms control, and regional security. Both countries pledged not to allow their territories to be used against each other. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The pact, seen as a response to Western sanctions, notably excludes a mutual defense clause. Since the war started in 2022, Russia and Iran have gotten closer. Tehran has supplied Moscow with many Shahed drones for attacks on Ukrainian infrastructure, as well as short-range ballistic missiles. Russia made a similar agreement with North Korea in June 2024.</p>
        </mj-text>
